To examine the applicability of the developed method, the limit of detection (LOD) was calculated to be in the range of 0.1–200 μM Cys concentration. A good linear relationship was obtained, which obeyed Beer's law with R2 = 0.991. The limit of quantification (LOQ) and detection (LOD) of the Cys was found to be 0.144 and 0.043 μM, respectively (Fig. 3b). It is worth mentioning here that in biological samples, the reported concentration of Cys is around 100 μM [41] thus the sensitivity of recognition of the proposed sensor is suitable for biological samples. Moreover, the linear range and LOD of the proposed probe were also compared with other reported methods (Table 2
                        ). LOD of the present study was even more sensitive than very recently described fluorescent probes utilizing the Ag/Au nanoclusters with reported LOD 80 and 1.1 μM [36,42], and carbon nanofibres (CNF) electrode 20 μM [40]. The binding stoichiometry was also studied by varying the volume ratio of Cys and McAgNPs by keeping the same concentration of both solutions (Fig. 4
                        ). Obtained results revealed that the stable complex of Cys and McAgNPs was formed when 1 mol of Cys react with 1 mol of McAgNPs (i.e. 1:1 ratio).
